VALUES
(55, 1, 1, 58, 9, 15, 15, 'promise of life which is in Christ Jesus', 'Connection of Promises in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of life and eternal inheritance through Christ. The promise in 2 Timothy relates to the eternal inheritance mentioned in Hebrews, highlighting the continuity of God''s promise through Jesus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 1, 43, 17, 3, 3, 'promise of life which is in Christ Jesus', 'Eternal Life Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''life'' in both passages. 2 Timothy speaks of the ''promise of life'' in Christ, while John defines eternal life as knowing God and Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 1, 43, 10, 28, 28, 'promise of life which is in Christ Jesus', 'Promise of Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of eternal life present in both passages. Paul refers to the ''promise of life which is in Christ Jesus,'' while Jesus assures believers of ''eternal life'' that cannot be taken away.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 1, 47, 1, 1, 1, 'an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Paul’s role as ''an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God.'' This connection highlights the continuity of Paul’s apostolic authority in his letters to different churches.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 1, 62, 5, 11, 13, 'promise of life which is in Christ Jesus', 'Eternal Life in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of eternal life found in both passages. Paul speaks of the ''promise of life which is in Christ Jesus,'' while John emphasizes that ''this life is in his Son.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 1, 49, 3, 6, 6, 'promise of life which is in Christ Jesus', 'Promise of Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the promise found in Christ. In 2 Timothy, Paul speaks of the ''promise of life which is in Christ Jesus,'' while Ephesians highlights being partakers of ''his promise in Christ.'' This connection highlights the shared theme of the promise associated with Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 1, 56, 1, 2, 2, 'promise of life which is in Christ Jesus', 'Promise of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of life and eternal life, linking them through the assurance given by God. This connection highlights the hope believers have in the life promised through Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 2, 55, 2, 1, 1, 'grace', 'Connection of Grace in Timothy', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of grace, with the first verse introducing grace as a gift from God and the second urging Timothy to be strong in that same grace. This connection highlights the importance of grace in Timothy''s spiritual life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 2, 54, 1, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection between Timothy Passages', 'Both passages emphasize Timothy''s relationship with Paul as a son in the faith. They also share the same greeting of grace, mercy, and peace from God and Christ.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 2, 44, 16, 1, 1, 'my dearly beloved son', 'Connection Between Timothy''s Identity', 'This connection highlights Timothy''s relationship with Paul as a beloved son in the faith. Both passages emphasize Timothy''s significance in the early church, with 2 Timothy addressing him directly and Acts introducing him as a disciple.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 2, 45, 1, 7, 7, 'Grace, mercy, and peace', 'Grace and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace from God. They share similar greetings, highlighting a common theme of divine favor and relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 2, 45, 12, 19, 19, 'dearly beloved', 'Connection of Beloved and Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the term ''dearly beloved,'' highlighting a sense of community and care. Additionally, they address the theme of responding to wrongdoing, with Romans urging against personal vengeance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 2, 50, 4, 1, 1, 'dearly beloved', 'Beloved Connections in Letters', 'Both passages emphasize the term ''dearly beloved,'' highlighting a deep affection between the authors and their recipients. This connection illustrates the theme of love and encouragement in the relationships within the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 45, 1, 8, 9, 'without ceasing I have remembrance of thee', 'Prayer and Thanksgiving Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of giving thanks and making mention of others in prayer without ceasing. This connection highlights a shared theme of devotion and remembrance in the context of prayer.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 58, 13, 8, 8, 'without ceasing I have remembrance', 'Faithfulness Across Time', 'This connection highlights the theme of unwavering faithfulness in both passages. In 2 Timothy, the remembrance in prayers reflects a consistent relationship with God, while Hebrews emphasizes the unchanging nature of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 44, 23, 1, 1, 'pure conscience', 'Conscience and Faithfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of living with a ''pure conscience'' before God. Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining a good conscience in one''s service and prayers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 44, 24, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Worship and Heritage', 'This connection highlights the theme of serving God with a pure conscience and the acknowledgment of a shared heritage. Both passages emphasize the importance of worshiping the God of one''s forefathers, linking personal faith to ancestral beliefs.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 54, 1, 5, 5, 'pure conscience', 'Connection of Pure Conscience', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of a pure conscience in serving God and fulfilling the commandment. This connection highlights the role of a pure heart and good conscience in the believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 54, 1, 19, 19, 'pure conscience', 'Faith and Conscience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of a good conscience in relation to faith. In 2 Timothy, the speaker expresses a pure conscience in prayer, while 1 Timothy warns against neglecting it, leading to a shipwreck of faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 3, 55, 3, 15, 15, 'remembrance of thee in my prayers', 'Connection of Faith and Scripture', 'This connection highlights the importance of prayer and scripture in developing faith. The remembrance in prayers from the first passage complements the knowledge of the holy scriptures in the second, emphasizing their role in salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 4, 55, 4, 9, 9, 'being mindful of thy tears', 'Desire for Companionship', 'Both passages emphasize a longing for connection, as seen in the desire to see each other. The mention of ''diligence to come shortly'' reflects the urgency of this companionship.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 4, 50, 1, 8, 8, 'greatly desiring to see thee', 'Longing and Affection in Letters', 'This connection highlights the deep emotional longing expressed by both authors. In 2 Timothy, the phrase ''greatly desiring to see thee'' parallels the sentiment in Philippians of longing ''after you all.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 4, 55, 4, 21, 21, 'mindful of thy tears', 'Emotional Bonds and Urgency', 'Both passages emphasize a longing for connection, with the first expressing a desire to see someone due to their tears, and the second urging a visit before winter. This connection highlights the emotional ties and urgency in relationships.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 4, 19, 126, 5, 5, 'mindful of thy tears', 'Connection of Tears and Joy', 'This connection highlights the theme of emotional experiences leading to joy. Both passages emphasize the significance of tears in the process of reaping joy.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 4, 23, 61, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Mourning and Joy', 'This connection highlights the theme of mourning and the subsequent joy that can arise from it. Both passages address the emotional state of individuals experiencing sorrow and the hope for transformation into joy.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 4, 24, 31, 13, 13, 'mindful of thy tears', 'Connection of Mourning and Joy', 'This connection highlights the transition from sorrow to joy. Both passages emphasize the theme of comfort and rejoicing after mourning.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 54, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Unfeigned Faith', 'Both passages emphasize ''faith unfeigned,'' highlighting the importance of genuine faith in the lives of believers. The mention of faith in both contexts suggests a thematic link between personal faith and the broader commandment of love.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 44, 16, 1, 1, 'unfeigned faith that is in thee', 'Timothy''s Faith Heritage', 'This connection highlights Timothy''s faith lineage, as 2 Timothy 1:5 mentions his grandmother Lois and mother Eunice, while Acts 16:1 identifies Timothy''s mother as a Jewish believer. Both passages emphasize the importance of familial faith in Timothy''s spiritual development.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 55, 3, 15, 15, 'unfeigned faith that is in thee', 'Faith and Knowledge of Scriptures', 'This connection highlights the progression of faith from family to individual. Both passages emphasize the importance of faith and knowledge of the holy scriptures in the development of Timothy''s spiritual life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 54, 4, 6, 6, 'remembrance', 'Faith and Remembrance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of remembrance in nurturing faith. The unfeigned faith in Timothy''s lineage connects to the call to remind others of good doctrine.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 45, 15, 14, 14, 'unfeigned faith that is in thee', 'Faith and Goodness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being filled with goodness and faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of inner qualities that enable believers to support and admonish one another.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 47, 6, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Unfeigned Love and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''unfeigned'' qualities in both passages. 2 Timothy emphasizes ''unfeigned faith'' passed through generations, while 2 Corinthians speaks of ''love unfeigned,'' suggesting a parallel in the authenticity of faith and love.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 5, 55, 1, 12, 12, 'unfeigned faith that is in thee', 'Faith and Assurance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of faith and assurance. In 2 Timothy 1:5, the unfeigned faith is highlighted, while 2 Timothy 1:12 expresses confidence in what has been committed to God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 6, 54, 4, 14, 14, 'the gift of God, which is in thee', 'Connection of Spiritual Gifts', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the gift of God within Timothy, highlighting the laying on of hands as a significant act in its impartation. This connection underscores the responsibility Timothy has to actively engage with and not neglect this gift.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 6, 60, 4, 10, 11, 'stir up the gift of God', 'Connection of Spiritual Gifts', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of using spiritual gifts. 2 Timothy encourages stirring up the gift of God, while 1 Peter instructs believers to minister their gifts to others. This connection highlights the communal aspect of utilizing God''s gifts.', 'theme', 0.615, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 6, 45, 12, 6, 8, 'stir up the gift of God', 'Connection of Spiritual Gifts', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual gifts and their activation. Both passages emphasize the importance of utilizing and stirring up the gifts given by God for ministry and service.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 6, 52, 5, 19, 19, 'stir up the gift of God', 'Stirring Up the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the importance of actively engaging with the Spirit of God. Both passages emphasize the necessity of not neglecting or suppressing the gifts and presence of the Holy Spirit in believers'' lives.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 6, 61, 3, 1, 1, NULL, 'Remembrance and Stirring Up Gifts', 'Both passages emphasize the act of stirring up remembrance, highlighting the importance of recalling spiritual gifts and truths. This connection showcases a shared theme of encouraging believers to actively engage with their faith.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
