(55, 1, 6, 61, 1, 12, 12, 'put thee in remembrance', 'Remembrance of Spiritual Gifts', 'This connection highlights the theme of remembrance in both passages. 2 Timothy emphasizes stirring up the gift of God, while 2 Peter stresses the importance of reminding believers of established truths.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 20, 2, 7, 7, 'sound mind', 'Connection of Wisdom and Sound Mind', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''sound'' in both passages. 2 Timothy emphasizes a ''sound mind,'' while Proverbs speaks of ''sound wisdom,'' suggesting a relationship between mental clarity and divine guidance.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 20, 8, 14, 14, 'sound mind', 'Connection of Strength and Wisdom', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of strength and soundness of mind. 2 Timothy highlights a spirit of power and a sound mind, while Proverbs speaks of strength and sound wisdom, suggesting a link between divine empowerment and wise counsel.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 38, 4, 6, 6, 'spirit of fear', 'Connection of Spirit and Strength', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the spirit in overcoming challenges. 2 Timothy highlights the spirit of power, while Zechariah underscores that strength comes not from might but from the spirit.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 42, 10, 19, 19, 'spirit of fear', 'Connection of Power and Fearlessness', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine empowerment in both passages. 2 Timothy 1:7 emphasizes that God provides a spirit of power, while Luke 10:19 speaks of the power given to believers to overcome adversaries without fear.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 43, 14, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Fear and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the absence of fear and the presence of peace. 2 Timothy speaks of a spirit of power, love, and a sound mind, while John assures believers not to let their hearts be troubled or afraid.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 44, 1, 8, 8, 'spirit of fear; but of power', 'Connection of Power and Witness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of power given by God. In 2 Timothy, the spirit of power is mentioned, while Acts highlights receiving power through the Holy Ghost for witnessing.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 7, 45, 8, 15, 15, 'spirit of fear', 'Connection of Fear and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the absence of fear in the believer''s life. 2 Timothy highlights the spirit of power, love, and a sound mind, while Romans speaks of not receiving a spirit of bondage to fear, but rather a Spirit of adoption.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 45, 1, 16, 16, 'not thou therefore ashamed of the testimony', 'Connection of Gospel and Shame', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of not being ashamed of the gospel. They highlight the power of God associated with the gospel and the call to endure afflictions for it.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 41, 8, 38, 38, 'ashamed of the testimony of our Lord', 'Connection of Shame and Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of shame associated with the testimony of Jesus. 2 Timothy encourages believers not to be ashamed of their faith, while Mark warns that being ashamed of Jesus will have consequences.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 55, 4, 5, 5, 'afflictions of the gospel', 'Afflictions and Ministry Work', 'Both passages emphasize enduring afflictions in the context of ministry. The call to ''endure afflictions'' in 2 Timothy 4:5 directly relates to the encouragement to ''partaker of the afflictions'' in 2 Timothy 1:8.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 60, 4, 13, 15, 'partaker of the afflictions of the gospel', 'Suffering for the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of sharing in sufferings for the sake of Christ. They encourage believers to embrace afflictions and rejoice in their participation in Christ''s sufferings.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 66, 12, 11, 11, 'the testimony of our Lord', 'Connection of Testimony and Affliction', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of testimony in the face of suffering. 2 Timothy encourages sharing the gospel despite afflictions, while Revelation highlights overcoming through testimony and sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 55, 1, 12, 12, 'be thou partaker of the afflictions', 'Connection of Shame and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of not being ashamed in the face of suffering for the gospel. The first passage encourages participation in afflictions, while the second asserts confidence in belief despite suffering.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 8, 49, 3, 1, 1, 'his prisoner', 'Connection of Paul''s Imprisonment', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as a prisoner, highlighting his suffering for the gospel. This connection underscores the shared theme of enduring afflictions for the sake of Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 9, 49, 2, 8, 9, 'according to his own purpose and grace', 'Salvation by Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize salvation as a gift from God, not based on human works. They highlight the role of grace in the process of salvation, underscoring that it is God''s purpose and grace that saves us.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 9, 56, 3, 4, 5, 'not according to our works', 'Salvation and Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize salvation not based on human works but on God''s purpose and mercy. They highlight the divine initiative in calling and saving believers, underscoring the role of grace in the process.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 9, 49, 1, 3, 4, 'before the world began', 'Divine Purpose and Calling', 'Both passages emphasize God''s purpose and grace given to believers before the world began. They highlight the idea of being chosen and called to holiness in Christ, underscoring a divine plan established prior to creation.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 9, 45, 11, 5, 6, 'not according to our works', 'Connection of Grace and Works', 'Both passages emphasize that salvation is not based on works but on grace. This connection highlights the concept of being called according to God''s purpose, which aligns with the election of grace in Romans.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 9, 45, 16, 25, 25, 'which was given us in Christ Jesus before the world began', 'Connection of Purpose and Mystery', 'This connection highlights the themes of divine purpose and grace that were established before the world began. Both passages emphasize the idea of a mystery that was kept secret, linking God''s plan to the calling and salvation in Christ.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 9, 60, 2, 20, 21, 'called us with an holy calling', 'Calling and Suffering Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being called by God, as seen in both passages. 2 Timothy emphasizes a holy calling according to God''s purpose, while 1 Peter discusses being called to endure suffering for righteousness.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
