(55, 1, 10, 56, 2, 11, 11, 'appearing of our Saviour Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Salvation and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the appearance of salvation through Jesus Christ. 2 Timothy highlights the manifestation of the Savior, while Titus speaks of the grace that brings salvation appearing to all men.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 10, 61, 3, 18, 18, 'our Saviour Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus Christ as Saviour, highlighting the importance of growing in knowledge and grace through Him. The manifestation of Christ in 2 Timothy connects to the call to know Him in 2 Peter.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 10, 46, 15, 26, 26, 'hath abolished death', 'Connection Between Death and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the defeat of death. 2 Timothy 1:10 speaks of Jesus abolishing death, while 1 Corinthians 15:26 identifies death as the last enemy to be destroyed.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 10, 58, 2, 14, 15, 'hath abolished death', 'Connection of Death and Deliverance', 'Both passages emphasize the defeat of death through Jesus Christ. 2 Timothy highlights how Christ abolished death, while Hebrews explains how He destroyed the devil''s power over death, delivering humanity from its fear.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(55, 1, 10, 45, 2, 7, 7, 'immortality', 'Connection of Immortality Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of immortality. In 2 Timothy, immortality is brought to light through the gospel, while Romans speaks of seeking immortality through well-doing.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
